This paper deals with the analysis of online conversations related to genetic testing on two popular platforms, Reddit and 4chan. The paper uses natural language processing and computer vision tools to identify trends, themes, and topics of discussion. The paper also highlights the use of genetic testing by alt-right groups to attack minorities and prove their genetic "purity." Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
